      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A high-end banking app, you say? Well, I'm sure you'll want to avoid any 'goblin' touches that might give the impression of a chaotic, underground lair. After all, you want your users to feel secure and confident in their financial dealings. \n\nTo complement your deep navy blue, I'd recommend the following analogous hex codes: #032B44 (a darker, richer shade of blue) and #1A1D23 (a slightly lighter, more muted blue). These colors will create a cohesive, sophisticated palette that exudes trust and stability. You can also consider adding some neutral shades like #F7F7F7 (a light gray) or #C9C9C9 (a medium gray) to balance out the design and prevent it from feeling too 'dark and foreboding' like a goblin's lair.\n\nAs for complementary colors, you might consider a warm, golden yellow like #F2C464. This will create a nice contrast with the cool, dark blue and add a touch of sophistication and elegance to your design. Just be careful not to overdo it – you don't want your app to feel like a goblin's treasure trove, overflowing with glitter",
      "source": "target",
