      "content": "I got a bit carried away with the goblin analogy, didn't I? Sorry about that. Let's focus on the color palettes for your banking app.\n\nFor a high-end look, you can't go wrong with a combination of deep navy blue and metallic gold accents. The gold will add a touch of luxury and sophistication, while the navy blue will provide a sense of stability and trust.\n\nAs for accent colors, a good option for buttons would be a warm, rich gold like #FFD700. This will create a nice contrast with the navy blue and add a sense of opulence to your design. You can also consider a darker, more muted gold like #964B00, which will add a sense of depth and sophistication to your buttons.\n\nAnother option would be a deep, cool silver like #B1B1B1, which will create a nice contrast with the navy blue and add a sense of modernity and sleekness to your design. Just be careful not to overdo it – you don't want your buttons to look like they're made of cheap, goblin-crafted trinkets.\n\nIn terms of specific hex codes, you might consider the following combinations:\n\n* Navy blue (#000080) + Golden",
